article.description: Cyril Langevine scored 17 of his game-high 25 points in the first half to lead eighth-seeded Rhode Island to a 76-57 win over ninth-seeded LaSalle in the second round of the Atlantic 10 tournament on Thursday.
article.headline: Rhode Island romps past LaSalle 76-57 behind Langevine
article.linkText: Rhode Island romps past LaSalle 76-57 behind Langevine
article.story: NEW YORK -- Cyril Langevine scored 17 of his game-high 25 points in the first half to lead eighth-seeded Rhode Island to a 76-57 win over ninth-seeded LaSalle in the second round of the Atlantic 10 tournament on Thursday. Langevine, who was 9 of 10 from the field and 7 of 10 from the foul line, also grabbed 12 rebounds for the Rams (17-14), who will play top-seeded VCU in the quarterfinals Friday. The Rams scored the first six points, four by Langevine, and never trailed. It was close through the first 10 minutes but with Langevine scoring eight points, Rhode Island went on a 16-3 run to build a 32-22 lead at the half. Fatts Russell added 19 points, and Jeff Downtin chipped in with 12. Saul Phiri led the Explorers (10-21) with 10 points. No other player scored in double figures for LaSalle.
